    "body": "### Describe the bug\r\n\r\nWhen installing node-sass into a CRA with typescript project, in usually integrates node-sass automatically for you. Recently mkdirp in the deps is failing and not removing certain files. This is causing the entire module tree to break. \r\n\r\n### Did you try recovering your dependencies?\r\n\r\nI did, and it resolves it, so this is a CRA issue not node-sass.\r\n\r\n### Environment\r\n\r\nWindows 10 Home, version 2004 build 19041.\r\nChrome browser.\r\nNode-sass version: 4.14.1\r\nCRA version: 3.4.1\r\nNodeJS version: 13.9.0\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Run: npx create-react-app <name> --typescript\r\n2. Run: npm i node-sass\r\n3. Run: npm run start (alternatively VSC recognises the errors in any import of react)\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nNode-sass should automatically install safely and allow the use of SCSS files.\r\n\r\n### Actual behavior\r\n\r\nInstalls after a very long period, but leaves a plethora of errors that mkdir (a dependency of CRA or node-sass) is unable to remove files? The files are some other modules. I would post a picture but it's crashing my PC at the minute when I attempt to install it freshly. \r\n\r\n### Reproducible demo\r\n\r\nAs mentioned above, it's literally crashing my PC unfortunately. If anyone could create the reproducible demo by just simple creating cra with TS and then install node-sass and running the app I'd greatly appreciate it!\r\n"
