    "body": "Using CRA and Typescript, I'm unable to utilize a Babel macro, which doesn't get resolved correctly.\r\n\r\nI have other two projects in JS in which I have no issues whatsoever with 3.4.1, but this one does not resolve the macro path properly.\r\n\r\nCurious thing is that if I remove the `.macro` extension from the macro file, it gets resolved (Of course macro will complain, but was just to test if the file was being found). This tells me that the `.macro` file is being found but something goes wrong after that.\r\n\r\nI have this example from `babel-plugin-macros` docs and it doesn't work as well, although is just JS: https://codesandbox.io/s/cra-macro-example-2hrpy?file=/src/evil.macro.js\r\n\r\nAny idea what could be wrong here?\r\n\r\nUnfortunately I cannot share my project, I can share the configuration.\r\n\r\n`tsconfig.json`:\r\n```\r\n{\r\n  \"compilerOptions\": {\r\n    \"target\": \"ES6\",\r\n    \"types\": [\"node\", \"jest\"],\r\n    \"lib\": [\"DOM\", \"DOM.Iterable\", \"ES6\"],\r\n    \"allowJs\": true,\r\n    \"checkJs\": false,\r\n    \"declaration\": false,\r\n    \"experimentalDecorators\": false,\r\n    \"alwaysStrict\": true,\r\n    \"importHelpers\": true,\r\n    \"noEmitHelpers\": true,\r\n    \"esModuleInterop\": true,\r\n    \"allowSyntheticDefaultImports\": true,\r\n    \"forceConsistentCasingInFileNames\": true,\r\n    \"module\": \"esnext\",\r\n    \"moduleResolution\": \"Node\",\r\n    \"resolveJsonModule\": true,\r\n    \"isolatedModules\": true,\r\n    \"noEmit\": true,\r\n    \"noEmitOnError\": false,\r\n    \"noFallthroughCasesInSwitch\": true,\r\n    \"noUnusedLocals\": false,\r\n    \"noUnusedParameters\": false,\r\n    \"removeComments\": true,\r\n    \"pretty\": true,\r\n    \"jsx\": \"preserve\",\r\n    \"sourceMap\": true,\r\n    \"baseUrl\": \"./src\",\r\n    \"typeRoots\": [\"./types\", \"./node_modules/@types\"],\r\n    \"strict\": true,\r\n    \"skipLibCheck\": true\r\n  },\r\n  \"include\": [\"src\", \"plopfile.js\"],\r\n  \"exclude\": [\"node_modules\", \"typings\", \"**/*.spec.ts\"]\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n`src/macros/tag.macro.js`:\r\n```\r\nconst { createMacro } = require('babel-plugin-macros');\r\nfunction myMacro (message: string) {\r\n   return message;\r\n}\r\nmodule.exports = createMacro(myMacro);\r\n```\r\n\r\nError:\r\n```\r\nCannot find module 'macros/tag.macro'\r\n```\r\n\r\nI have other files referring to the project root `src`, like `components`, and all of those work just fine, it seems related to the `.macro` extension.\r\n\r\nAny help of what could be wrong?"
